<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Yeah, but that's a paladin's thing-we're defensive tanks- we never expect to outdamage our melee counterparts. imagine this with a Sarnak Battle Shield (25ac +stats) or a Bladestopper. I'd take this thing over any 2hander, and that includes FA.  BTW, I damage more with a Ghoulbane and FBSS than I do with Mith 2h and TBB- it's all about speed- more chances to hit.  As for not duel wielding- bah to duel wielding.  A paladin's strength is in one blade, not two- any more would weaken his resolution.  BTW, I average at least 25 dmg bashing with a 12ac shield- we're not the main battle tanks, we get the stuns running so the casters can nooook ;)<BR>
Lydirn Whiteheart<BR>
